gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bucks 128, Rockets 119
gameRecap.excerpt: The Bucks won their fourth game in a row as they defeated the Rockets, 128-119. Damian Lillard led the Bucks with 39 points (5-8 3PT) and 11 assists as Giannis Antetokounmpo added 26 points and 17 rebounds. Fred VanVleet (22 points, six assists) and Alperen Sengun (20 points, eight rebounds, five assists) led the Rockets in the loss. The Bucks move to 18-7 as the Rockets have their five-game win streak snapped and move to 13-10.
